ominant power in satellite internet technology. The ways he is wielding that influence are raising global alarms. （ <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2023/07/28/business/starlink.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">纽约时报</a>）</p><p> • <strong>How John Fetterman Came Out of the Darkness</strong> : When he looks back on the past year—a year in which he nearly died, became a US Senator, and nearly died again—it is the debate that John Fetterman identifies as the breaking point. ( <a href="https://time.com/6296038/john-fetterman-depression-cover-story/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Time</a> )</p><p> • <strong>A Requiem for the Dead</strong> : Dead and Company—the most successful and longest-running post-Jerry configuration of Grateful Dead members—has purportedly given up the road. We took one last trip to Shakedown Street to make sense of what it all meant and what it means if they&#39;re done.. ( <a href="https://www.theringer.com/music/2023/7/27/23808537/grateful-dead-and-company-final-tour-john-mayer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Ringer</a> )</p></blockquote><p>请务必在下周与丹·哈里斯 (Dan Harris) 一起观看我们的<a href="https://ritholtz.com/category/podcast/mib/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-web-url="http://www.bloombergview.com/topics/masters-in-business">商业硕士课程</a>，丹·哈里斯是一名记者，曾两次获得艾美奖获奖电视记者，其中包括 ABC 新闻、今晚世界新闻、夜线和早安美国的当地新闻。他从巴格达报道伊拉克战争，并因其对卡特里娜飓风的报道而被授予著名的爱德华·R·默罗奖。他还是《纽约<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0062917609/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>时报》畅销书《10%快乐：我如何驯服头脑中的声音》、《在不失去优势的情况下减轻压力》和《找到真正有效的自助——一个真实的故事》的作者。</em></a>他现在<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://wondery.com/shows/ten-percent-happier-with-dan-harris/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>与 Dan Harris 一起主持 Wondery, Ten Percent Happier</em></a>播客。</p><p></p><p> <strong>Which G7 Economies Have the Highest Inflation?</strong><br /> <a href="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/highestinflation-2.png" target="_blank" 